        <!-- Key Learnings -->
        <section class="section">
            <h2>Key Takeaways</h2>
            <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0;">
                <li style="padding: 1rem; background: #f8f9fa; margin-bottom: 1rem; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid #667eea;">
                    <strong>Mobile-first approach</strong> led to cleaner, more maintainable code and better performance on all devices.
                </li>
                <li style="padding: 1rem; background: #f8f9fa; margin-bottom: 1rem; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid #667eea;">
                    <strong>Accessibility testing early</strong> prevented major refactoring later in the development process.
                </li>
                <li style="padding: 1rem; background: #f8f9fa; margin-bottom: 1rem; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid #667eea;">
                    <strong>CSS Grid and Flexbox</strong> combination provided the most flexible and responsive layout solution.
                </li>
                <li style="padding: 1rem; background: #f8f9fa; margin-bottom: 1rem; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid #667eea;">
                    <strong>Progressive enhancement</strong> ensured the component worked even when JavaScript failed to load.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>
